<div class="prose">
  <p>Case studies are how you turn a hazard claim into a defensible one. "Tōhoku was bad" doesn't earn a high T/T band on the <a href="/foundations/the-rubric/">rubric</a>. "Tōhoku showed that seawalls sized for expected events fail at actual M9 run-up heights" does. Read the entry, pick the specific evidence, cite it.</p>
</div>

